Class ULPFCmp

java.lang.Object
  uk.ac.macaulay.util.AbstractFloatingPointComparison
      uk.ac.macaulay.util.ULPFCmp
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.util.Comparator<java.lang.Number>, FloatingPointComparison
public class ULPFCmp
extends AbstractFloatingPointComparison

ULPFCmp A floating-point comparison class based on Math.ulp(). This is an implementation of the principles outlined in a developerWorks article by Elliotte Rusty Harold in which the recommended JUnit test for floating-point equality is assertEquals(expectedValue, actualValue, 5 * Math.ulp(expectedValue)) This introduces asymmetry in the tests, since one of the arguments will be used to derive the tolerance, and the other won't. In the methods of this class, it is always the first argument (a) that is assumed to be the expectedValue.

Author:
Gary Polhill
